02:14:13,408 --> 02:14:20,173
So as I laid out in my memorandum that accompanied the application, 86 Orchard Street is in a GR district.

1370
02:14:20,373 --> 02:14:26,257
It is a residential property that has been used for a very long time, has a three family.

1371
02:14:26,277 --> 02:14:32,622
And to evidence that I've provided with the memorandum,

1372
02:14:34,203 --> 02:14:36,064
voting records that go back to 1928.

1373
02:14:38,245 --> 02:14:55,531
And when you look through those records, what you see consistently is three sets of tenants at the property, either individual tenants in an apartment or a married couple based on the same last name or kin.

1374
02:14:57,492 --> 02:15:03,576
And that seems to have been, as I said, a continuous use all through up to the present time.

1375
02:15:04,396 --> 02:15:12,001
Supplementing the voting records, I've also provided a copy of a letter from a longtime tenant in

1376
02:15:13,663 --> 02:15:27,773
Natasha Merkulov, which is part of the package that I submitted, evidencing her statement that it's been used as a three-family for the entire time of her tenancy.

1377
02:15:29,014 --> 02:15:32,156
